<recipe lang="en-uk" xmlns:lxslt="http://xml.apache.org/xslt">
<title><![CDATA[Eel and Broccoli Pie / Impanata di Caltanissetta]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[A Christmas dish. The original is made with two (or three) impanatas layered inside each other.]]></description>
<source/>
<img></img>
<cuisine>
<style>Italian</style>
<region>Sicilian</region>
<approach/>
</cuisine>
<tags>
<tag>Pie</tag>
</tags>
<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[dissolve fresh yeast in warm water for 5m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add flour bit by bit and knead for 10m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[rest in greased bowl, covered in kitchen towel until doubled in size, about 2h]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[sauté onion in olive oil med for 10m. Add eel, tomatoes on low heat for 10m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[put anchovy fillets in a skillet]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add onion, caciocavallo cheese, half the black olives]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[lay broccoli on top]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[drizzle olive oil on top]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add black olives on top]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add salt]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[drizzle red wine on top]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[cover and simmer without stirring on low heat for 12m]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Drain and mix with the tomatoes]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Roll out the dough in a disk, ladle out the drained fillings, fold like a calzone, and puncture.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Bake until ready 190° for 35m]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
